From 11c3643562e314d60c07afb6f1fec25875e48d62 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: adeheldb <andre.deheldbadur@windriver.com>
Date: Wed, 17 Jun 2026 13:50:42 -0300
Subject: [PATCH] Add statistics and monitoring interfaces

Add statistics and monitoring interfaces

Update or create management interfaces in linuxptp daemons to expose
synchronization data that was previously internal-only.

Features:

1. OFFSET_STATS_NP management TLV (ptp4l, MID 0xC100)
   New clock-level GET-only TLV exposing offset statistics (min, max,
   mean, stddev, rms, num_samples) cached from the existing
   summary_interval computation. Returns all-zero with num_samples=0
   when summary_interval <= 0 or no samples have accumulated.

2. sync_lost field in PORT_SERVICE_STATS_NP (ptp4l)
   Appends a uint64 sync_lost counter to the existing per-port service
   stats TLV. Counts forward gaps in Sync message sequence numbers
   using uint16 modular arithmetic with a 32768 half-window threshold.
   Resets to zero on daemon restart.

3. phc2sys monitoring socket (/var/run/phc2sys-mon-<instance>)
   New unconditional SOCK_STREAM JSON socket (mode 0666), independent
   of the existing HA socket. Responds to {"command":"stats"} with
   servo offset, delay, servo state, and clock source.

4. ts2phc monitoring socket (/var/run/ts2phc-mon-<instance>)
   Same JSON protocol as phc2sys. Exposes PHC-to-external-source
   offset. Delay always reported as -1.

All four features are delivered as a single patch because they share
a common purpose: exposing internal synchronization state through
programmatic interfaces. They touch independent daemons with no shared
code, enabling a single apply/revert lifecycle.

TEST PLAN:
PASS: Build the linuxptp package on Trixie environment
PASS: Load engineer .deb file in Trixie system and verify
      OFFSET_STATS_NP functionality.
PASS: Load engineer .deb file in Trixie system and verify
      PORT_SERVICE_STATS_NP functionality.
PASS: Load engineer .deb file in Trixie system and verify
      SOCK_STREAM JSON functionality for phc2sys.
PASS: Load engineer .deb file in Trixie system and verify
      SOCK_STREAM JSON functionality for ts2phc.
PASS: Connect to phc2sys-mon socket without sending data for 5s.
      Second client query returns response within 2s. Daemon
      servo loop shows no interruption.
PASS: Connect to ts2phc-mon socket without sending data for 5s.
      Second client query returns response within 2s. Daemon
      servo loop shows no interruption.
PASS: 3 concurrent clients querying monitoring socket in a loop
      for 30s while ts2phc is actively syncing. No servo disruption
      or clock step observed.
PASS: kill -9 ts2phc, restart daemon. Monitoring socket is
      re-created and responds to queries (stale socket cleanup).
PASS: With ha_enabled=1, both phc2sys-mon-* and ha_phc2sys_com_socket
      coexist and respond independently.
PASS: With summary_interval=0, GET OFFSET_STATS_NP returns
      num_samples=0 and all fields zero.
PASS: Send unknown command {"command":"reset"} to monitoring socket.
      Daemon returns {"error":"unknown command"} and does not crash.
PASS: Send malformed non-JSON input to monitoring socket.
      Daemon returns {"error":"unknown command"} and does not crash.
PASS: phc2sys -a -r invoked without -f (no config file).
      Daemon does not segfault. Monitoring socket created at
      /var/run/phc2sys-mon-default.
PASS: Query phc2sys monitoring socket immediately after restart
      (before servo lock). Returns {"error":"no servo data"}.

Signed-off-by: adeheldb <andre.deheldbadur@windriver.com>

